div1.p:
JOHN BLACKLING sworn. - On the 28th of March I lost two pigs belonging to myself and Richard Hawkins;
John Allen
was convicted at the last Sessions of stealing them; I was present at the trial: On the 29th I went to Ducking-pond-lane, and looked through a hole into the stable, we saw the two pigs immediately; the stable belonged to the prisoner, as I understood; I knew them to be my pigs; I went off immediately to the Public-office, Lambeth-street, leaving two persons that were with me there; I thought two officers back with me, Nowland and Osmand; before I came back, Mr. Special had let these two persons in to see the pigs; the officers took the pigs into their care.

Mr. Alley contended that the indictment could not be maintained, inasmuch as it ought to have been charged to be the dwelling-house of the Company, and cited the case of
